Abortion is a controversial issue that has been in the news lately because someone at the Supreme Court leaked that Roe may be overturned in June. Roe is a Supreme Court decision that allows a woman to choose whether to have an abortion when she finds herself pregnant. It is up to states to decide whether to outlaw abortions. If Roe is overturned, many conservative states have indicated they will outlaw abortions.
I believe in a woman's right to chose. Fortunately, I live in Colorado whether abortions are legal. Pro-abortion legislation was just passed by the Colorado state legislature, which is overwhelming Democratic. About 60 percent of Americans support a woman's right to choose, but many Republicans, conservatives and Christians are passionately against abortion.
I support a woman's right to chose because being forced to carry a baby to term can impact women's careers and financial stability. It can also impact fathers who are not married to the mother because they are required to pay child support if DNA testing shows they are the father. Also if abortions are outlawed, many disabled and premature babies will be born. The government may end up paying for the care of these disabled children. 
When the Supreme Court decision comes out, the abortion issue will be front and center in this country.
